@startuml warning_hold_and_theme_stale_to_hud_clear_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Warning Hold And Theme Stale To HUD Clear Signal Flow\n(cluster warning + theme hold windows -> HUD warning clear and default brightness)

participant "Cluster warning bus" as Warn #F4F7FB
participant "Cluster theme bus" as Theme #E8F0FE
participant "HUD\nwarning-render owner" as HUD #E8F7E8
participant "HUD state bus" as HudBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers /\nvisual readers" as Obs #FCE8FF

== HUD Inputs ==

Warn -> HUD : frmClusterWarningMsg\nWarningTextCode
Theme -> HUD : frmClusterThemeMsg\nThemeMode / ClusterBrightness
activate HUD
HUD -> HUD : warningInputExpired =\nethIsRecentTick(gWarningRxMs, 1500)
HUD -> HUD : themeInputExpired =\nethIsRecentTick(gThemeRxMs, 1500)
HUD -> HUD : if warning expired then\nwarningCode = 0
HUD -> HUD : if theme expired then\nthemeMode = 0 / hudBrightness = 18
HUD -> HUD : hudMode falls back to 0\nwhen warningCode == 0 and no popup/guide override
note right of HUD
Representative gating inputs
- WarningTextCode
- ThemeMode
- ClusterBrightness
- warning/theme hold windows
end note

== HUD Publish ==

HUD -> HudBus : frmHudStateMsg\nHudMode / HudWarningCode / HudBrightness
note right of HUD
Representative outputs
- HudMode
- HudWarningCode
- HudBrightness
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

HudBus -> Obs : HUD clear/default visibility /\nvisual observers
deactivate HUD

note over Warn, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. Warning and theme context reach HUD
2. HUD evaluates hold-window expiry for warning and theme sources
3. HUD clears warning state and restores default brightness when sources expire
4. HUD publishes the cleared/default visual posture
end note

@enduml
